@startuml seq-bootstrap-lock
title Bootstrap-window lock v1.3.0 - requireBootstrapClientId end-to-end

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Orchestrator\n(e.g. management lib)" as App
participant "Source signer\n(signed-fetch / unsigned bootstrap)" as Signer
collections "Target API\n/api/internal/hmac" as Target
participant "handleInternalManagementRequest" as Handler
participant "verifyHttpSignature" as Verify
database "Redis (target)" as RedisTgt

note over Target
  Target initialized with
  initializeHmacHttpAuth({
    requireBootstrapClientId: "self_propagation_signer",
    internalManagementRoute: "/api/internal/hmac",
    ...
  }).
end note

== Phase A: orchestrator probes the locked target ==
App -> Signer : unsigned GET /api/internal/hmac
Signer -> Target : GET /api/internal/hmac
Target -> Handler : handleInternalManagementRequest({method:"GET",...})
Handler -> RedisTgt : clients.listClientIds()
RedisTgt --> Handler : [] (empty)
Handler -> Handler : bootstrapLocked =\nrequireBootstrapClientId !== undefined\n&& !knownClients.includes(requireBootstrapClientId)
note right of Handler
  GET stays open at all times so external
  orchestrators can detect the locked state
  without parsing error responses.
end note
Handler --> Target : 200 {ok, clientsCount:0,\n  authRequired:false, bootstrapLocked:true, ...}
Target --> App : 200 health body shows bootstrapLocked:true

== Phase B: hostile / mis-targeted POST during the lock ==
App -> Signer : unsigned POST /api/internal/hmac\n{clientId:"intruder", secret:"evil"}
Signer -> Target : POST /api/internal/hmac
Target -> Handler : handleInternalManagementRequest
Handler -> RedisTgt : clients.listClientIds()
RedisTgt --> Handler : [] (empty)
Handler -> Handler : bootstrapLocked = true
note right of Handler
  While locked: POST is accepted ONLY for
  payload.clientId === requireBootstrapClientId.
  Any other clientId returns 403 BOOTSTRAP_LOCKED.
end note
Handler --> Target : 403 {error:"BOOTSTRAP_LOCKED",\n  message:"API is locked until ..."}
Target --> App : 403 BOOTSTRAP_LOCKED

== Phase C: PUT / PATCH / DELETE refused while locked ==
App -> Signer : signed PUT / PATCH / DELETE /api/internal/hmac
Signer -> Target : PUT / PATCH / DELETE /api/internal/hmac
Target -> Handler : handleInternalManagementRequest
Handler -> Handler : bootstrapLocked = true\n&& method != "POST"
Handler --> Target : 403 BOOTSTRAP_LOCKED
Target --> App : 403 BOOTSTRAP_LOCKED

== Phase D: lock release via the named clientId ==
App -> Signer : unsigned POST /api/internal/hmac\n{clientId:"self_propagation_signer",\n  secret:"<plain>",\n  purpose:"propagation-only",\n  allowedIps:[]}
Signer -> Target : POST /api/internal/hmac
Target -> Handler : handleInternalManagementRequest
Handler -> RedisTgt : clients.listClientIds()
RedisTgt --> Handler : [] (still empty)
Handler -> Handler : bootstrapLocked = true\n&& method == "POST"\n&& payloadClientId == requireBootstrapClientId\n-> allowed
Handler -> RedisTgt : clients.setSecret(clientId, secret, ...,\n  {purpose:"propagation-only"})
RedisTgt --> Handler : stored
Handler --> Target : 201 {ok, operation:"create",\n  clientId:"self_propagation_signer", kind:"http"}
Target --> App : 201 created

== Phase E: business requests now succeed ==
App -> Signer : signed business request /secure/widgets\n(signed by another credential, not the propagation key)
Signer -> Target : signed request
Target -> Verify : verifyHttpSignature(...)
Verify -> RedisTgt : credentialStore.getClientRecord(\n  requireBootstrapClientId)
RedisTgt --> Verify : record (lock released)
note over Verify
  Lock re-checked on every verify call,
  so an operator-driven DELETE of the
  bootstrap credential re-locks the API
  on the next request.
end note
Verify --> Target : VerifiedHttpRequest
Target --> App : 200 business response

note over RedisTgt
  GET probe NOW returns:
  { authRequired:true, clientsCount:1,
    bootstrapLocked:false }
end note

@enduml
